es emergency back up care 16 hours of subsidized care per year for eligible employees new 2010 11 program includes eldercare for eligibility see the child care eligibility matrix for detailed eligibility criteria click on the individual programs above child care and parenting resources child care resource and referral child care data base babysitting list parent net email list serv parent education and consultation elder care services information and referral services through avenidas senior center consultations at a reduced rate on site monthly caregiver support group resources for long distance caregiving quarterly brown bag seminars on relevant topics lending library worklife navigating work and personal life personal consultations resource and referral to campus and community services quarterly brown bag seminars lending library gateways for students faculty staff post docs hospital staff hr managers others financial programs for employees centers stanford madera grove children's center application stanford arboretum children's center application cclc stanford west application children's center of the stanford community application rainbow school application peppertree after school program application bing nursery school stanford university worklife office 320 panama street bambi modular stanford california 94305 4160 650 723 2660 worklife office is a division of stanford human resources terms of use copyright complaints
